Special mentions:
- A whole new foot-print free induced pluripotent stem cell reprogramming technique enters the field: Measles-based reprogramming! Other available non-integrating techniques are mRNA-based, Sendai-virus, and episome. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.omta.2026.201723
- Primary γδ T cells are effective against CMV in solid organ transplant recipients. γδ T cells can be generated from iPSC, making them interesting candidates for off-the-shelf provision. https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-026-69538-2
- Macrophages, even in the absence of DC, can effectively present antigens to T-cells, enabling tumor immunity in the immune suppressed tumor microenvironment of hepatocellular carcinoma. This provides a strong rationale for macrophage tumor vaccines; which can be engineered from iPSC. https://doi.org/10.1158/1538-7445.AM2026-2920
